('63201-10220-99-017', '/', 'Millingtonia hortensis  L.f.', '', 'Indian cork tree', '', 'Tree', '             \r\n', 'The tree is native to South east Asia and India, often found in mixed deciduous and dry evergreen forests. It can grow well in humid atmosphere but can stand the heat. It can grow well in loamy sand.  \r\n', '      \r\n', 'Dry flowers when used as cigarettes can cure asthma. Roots also can be used to cure asthma, tuberculosis, and also good for lung health. Dry leaves are also used as cigarettes.   \r\n', '   \r\n', 'It can be used for decoration because of its beautiful appearance and floral fragrance.  The trunk, which is light yellow softwood, can be used in making furniture and corks. \r\n', '    10-40   6       5    4   1    ', 'The flower is white, scented and 10-40 cm long in tubular shape with 6 cm wide, facing down to the ground. It has five petals, four stamens, and a protruded corolla lobe.  The flowers occur in cluster at the end of twigs and they boom in the evenings until nighttime during the period September to Ma', '  30   1.5-2    2  \r\n', 'The fruit is long, thin flattened with 30 cm long and 1.5-2 wide. The ripped fruit splits into 2 sections, each having many seeds. \r\n', '    \r\n', 'The seed has a broad thin transparent wing which helps it easily get blown by the wind.  \r\n', '  6-15   100         \r\n', 'The trunk is medium sized, 6-15 m tall.  The trunk of a full-grown tree can be up to 100 cm in circumference.  The trunk is straight and thick, cracked, scaly, with yellowish grey barks and branches. Its branches which grow down make it an umbrella-shaped tree.', ' 2-3        \r\n', 'The leaf is bipinnate or tripinnate in opposite directions. The leaflet is ovate and lanceolate in shape and its rim is jagged, acute apex, and obtuse based. Its ventral surface has thick veins.   \r\n', '', ''),
