('63201-10220-99-002', '', '', '', '', '', 'Tree', '     ', 'Native to south east Asia.', '        ', 'The leaf has sedative and diuretic effects.  It also increases blood pressure and relieves dysmenorrhea. Curry with Thai copper pod leaves has a laxative effect and cures beriberi. The fruits and twigs are edible.', '', '', '   20-30   10-60   5    1.5-2.5    10    ', 'The flowers of  Thai Copper Pod are yellow in branched clusters at the end of twigs and 20-30 cm long. Each cluster has 10-60 flowers. The flower has 10 stamen and 5 obovate petals with 1.5-2.5 cm in diameter. The flowers bloom all year round. ', ' ', 'The pods are brown flat.', '  1-1.5 20-30   20-30 ', 'The pod has brown flat seeds, 1-1.5 cm wide and 20-30 cm long, containing 20-30 seeds.', '  8 - 15    ', 'It is an evergreen tree, 8-15 m high with a spreading crown. Its bark is grey and light brown and has vertical fissure on.  ', '   5-14   1-1.5  3-7     ', 'The tree has pinnately compound leaves of which the leaflets arrange in 5-14 pairs along a rachis. Each leaf is 3-7 cm long and 1-1.5 cm wide. The leaflet is elliptic with a rounded tip.  The leaflet is dark green and has tomentosus hair on its ventral surface.', '', ''),
