('63201-10220-99-009', '', 'Cerbera odollam Gaertn.', 'Gaertn.', 'Pong Pong', '', 'Tree', '                      ', 'It is native to Andaman archipelago, Bangladesh, India, Borneo, Cook islands, Cambodia, Java, Malaysia, Mariana islands, Burma, New Caledonia islands, Nicobar islands, the Philippines, Queensland, Samoa, Sri Lanka, Sumatra, Thailand, Tonga, Vanuatu, Vietnam, Trinidad and Tobago.', '         ', 'The root resolves flatulence. The bark and trunk are used to cure a cold and it also has a purgative effect. The leaves are used to cure a cold and relieve fever. The flowers, tasting bitter, are used to treat hemorrhoid. The seed is good for ones heart.', '  ', 'This tree is used for decoration and it provides shade.', '    3-5 .   5   5 ', 'The flower is white with 3-5 cm in diameter.  It grows in cluster at a terminal bud. The aestivation of a petal is sympetalous and tabular with 5 corolla lobes and 5 sepals.', '     6-10 .  ', 'The fruit is greenish round and luster-glossed with 6-10 cm in diameter. The ripped fruit turns greenish purple or dark purple.', '    \r\n', 'The seed has a broad thin transparent wing which helps it easily get blown by the wind.  \r\n', '   5-15 .      ', 'The trunk is small-sized. The tree is insidious, and its trunk is 5-15 m tall.  The trunk has a round crown spreading out elliptically. Every part of the trunk has white latex. The bark is greyish or light brown and smooth.', '     4-8 .  15-30 .     2-3 .', 'The leaf is simple.  And leaves are spirally arranged around branches. The leaf blade is lanceolate and obovate with 4-8 cm wide. The upper-side and under-side of the leaf are smooth. Its petiole is narrow, with 2-3 cm in length.  Its leaf apex is cuspidate.', '', ''),
